# OpenSCAD Docker wrapper

## How it works

`bin/openscad-docker` is a bash script that translates local `openscad` CLI calls into `docker run --rm` commands. It mounts the repo root at `/work` inside the container and rewrites file paths in the arguments.

## Usage

Set `OPENSCAD_EXEC` to the absolute path of the wrapper:
```bash
export OPENSCAD_EXEC="$(pwd)/bin/openscad-docker"
```

The Makefile does this automatically. `Scad_Renderer` reads `OPENSCAD_EXEC` from env.

## Path handling

- The wrapper detects file arguments by extension (.scad, .stl, .png) or path separators
- Host paths inside the repo root are rewritten to `/work/...`
- The repo root is bind-mounted via `--mount type=bind,source=...,target=/work`
- This handles the iCloud path with spaces correctly (--mount syntax, not -v)

## Scad_Renderer priority fix

Darwin `_try_detect_openscad_exec` now has `if self.openscad_exec is None` guard before trying `/Applications/OpenSCAD.app/...`, so `OPENSCAD_EXEC` env var always takes priority.

## Image

Default: `openscad/openscad:trixie.2025-12-15`. Override with `OPENSCAD_DOCKER_IMAGE` env var.
